        <Parent_String>Suidae (family) [300310427], Artiodactyla (order) [300310321], Mammalia (class) [300265707], Vertebrata (subphylum) [300265720], Chordata (phylum) [300266513], Animalia (kingdom) [300249395], Eukaryota (domain) [300265677], living organisms (entities) [300390503], Living Organisms (hierarchy name) [300265673], Agents Facet [300264089]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Genus containing at least 11 living and several fossil species of intelligent, social, even-toed ungulate having a stout body, sparse bristly hair, and a broad flat snout for rooting in the soil, including wild and domestic pigs.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>屬名，包括至少11個現存物種與數個化石種，是聰明、社會性的偶蹄類動物，具矮胖的軀體、稀疏的鬃毛、用於拱土的寬扁口鼻，分為野生豬與馴養豬。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Género que contiene al menos 11 especies vivas y varias especies fósiles de ungulados inteligentes, sociales y de dedos parejos que tienen un cuerpo robusto, pelo escaso y erizado, y un amplio hocico plano para echar raíces en el suelo, incluyendo cerdos salvajes y domésticos.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000320/GRI-FloCo</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109721/GRI, FloCo terminology (2019-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Pitzotl tlen oncah 11 tlamantli yoltoqueh huan miac tlamantli pitzomeh tlen quipiyah ininizte, teicneltzitzin huan ininizte cenca chihchicactic, iihhuiyo axmiac huan huihhuitztic, itencomich patlachtic para quicua inelhuayo xihuitl tlen onca ipan tlalli, calaquih cuapitzomeh tlen nemih cuatitlan huan pitzomeh tlen tlapiyalmeh.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Eastern Huasteca Nahuatl</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
